subject:

DECISIONS
===================================================================
verse:

All who believe in God’s Son have eternal life. Those who
don’t obey the Son will never experience eternal life, but
the wrath of God remains upon them. (Jn. 3:36)
===================================================================
reflection:

In this verse Jesus sets before us the greatest choice in
life. It is up to us to decide today whom we will obey
(Joshua 24:25), and God want us to choose Him and life
(Deut. 30:15-20. The wrath of God is God’s final judgement
and rejection of sinners. To put off the choice is to choose
not to follow Christ Indecision is a fatal decision.
===================================================================
prayer:

God of life, set before me the clear choice to follow You,
and give me courage to decide today. Break the grip of
indecision, turn my heart from sin, and lead me to obedience
that chooses life in Christ. Teach me to walk faithfully
now, not tomorrow, trusting Your mercy and truth. Amen. (AI)

===================================================================
